5:
Ah, crap. I got so pissed off I forgot
about Alk and Light.
10: Hey, Tiger! I've been looking for you!
13:
Oh, look at that. Does Daddy know
you're all the way out here on your
own?
16:
Shut it! You think I like having
someone like him as a father?
24:
Cause we left matters unfinished
back there!
27: Is that you or your old man talking?
31: Damn it... Fine, how about this.
37:
Fight me! If you don't, these two are
as good as dead!
50:
Oh no, oh dear! Nimbus, please help
me, I beg you!
56:
Y-yeah, help us, Nimbus, you're our
only hope. You have to fight him!
60:
You guys are seriously awful actors,
you know that?
68:
I mean, you seemed so serious, so
we figured we should play along.
72:
If you truly feel that fighting Nimbus
again will help you come to terms
with your emotions, you should do
so! Don't give up.
78:
Help me, Nimbus! I'm in so much
danger!
81: All right, enough already. I'll fight him.
85:
Hear that? It's on. But you better not
pull your punches—you gotta want
this, kid.
89:
I do. Screw my dad—I want to finish
this for my own sake!
93: So let's do it! Come at me, Tiger!
97:
If you're serious, then you're gonna
have to prove it to me!
105:
I believe this is where we left off last
time.
110:
Looks like I win.
"That'll teach you to mess with my
friends." There, are we done playing
pretend?
118:
There's no rule saying the first
person to fall down loses! We're not
in the ring anymore.
121:
This isn't an arena match—it's an
all-out fight. Or have you forgotten
what that means?
125:
All right, kid, I hear you loud and
clear. If it's a "proper" fight you want,
that's what I'll give you!
134:
Y-yeah... I guess so.
That was... what's the word?
139: I won't argue with you on that.
144:
I'm pretty sure they completely
forgot we were here.
148:
So long as they remember the
reason they chose to fight, I think
our little farce will have been worth it.
162:
Hmm... If my memory serves me, I
think the two of you are even in
terms of takedowns.
167:
D-damn... I need to do better than
that.
169:
You think if I stick around with you
guys, I can get even stronger?
174:
Why? What do you wanna
accomplish by getting stronger?
182:
If it helps you get over your daddy
issues, you're more than welcome to
join us, kid.
186:
Sh-shut the hell up! You're first on
my to-pummel list, you overgrown
housecat.
